examples.en: The fox was flushed from its cover.
The garbage flushed down the river
The sky flushed with rosy splendor.
His pulse was throbbing and his cheeks flushed.
She flushed the rest of her drink down the toilet.
Susan flushed deeply and looked away.
Armies were flushed with the conquest.
The birds were flushed from their hiding place.
He flushed a pheasant from a thicket of willows.
His face was flushed with excitement and his hands trembled.
The whole of the work is to be flushed up with mortar or cement.
He flushed the toilet (=made water go through the toilet to clean it).
The blood flushed in Eliza's pale face.
She flushed and her eyes fell (=she looked down).
He was flushed after getting out of the hot bath.
